MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Verified against live repo (25a45a4). 16 files still had false claims
after partial upload. This commit fixes all of them plus adds the
missing Tests/BiquadVsSvfComparison.cpp.

WHAT WAS WRONG (per JUCE forum holy-city, zsliu98, kerfuffle + r/DSP rb-j, SkoomaDentist):
- Paper/code claimed SVF eliminates BLT cramping that RBJ suffers from
- Fabricated measurement: RBJ gives +0.73 dB at fc=16kHz (-5.27 dB error)
- Fabricated measurement: RBJ@4x gives +4.82 dB
- SvfBiquad.h said 'de-cramped by design', '16 kHz: 214% severe (SVF: exactly 0%)'
- EQBand.h, PluginEditor.cpp, SvfTest.cpp, FeatureBench.cpp, EngineIsolationTest.cpp
  all described SVF as de-cramping
- All 5 LaTeX files: abstracts claimed SVF eliminates cramping, tables had
  fabricated -5.27 dB measurements

WHAT IS TRUE:
- Both SVF and RBJ use BLT with identical prewarping
- Both produce IDENTICAL steady-state responses (0.0000 dB diff at all freqs)
- BLT guarantees exact gain at fc for any correctly prewarped filter
- Cramping is a BLT property, not a topology property
- SVF advantages: modulation stability, lower automation noise, better
  coefficient interpolation for per-sample Dynamic EQ updates
  (per SkoomaDentist, r/DSP May 2026)

TESTS: ResponsePlotTest PASS, BiquadVsSvfComparison ALL PASSED (9 assertions),
SvfTest 11 PASS 0 FAIL

REFERENCES: zsliu98, holy-city, kerfuffle (JUCE forum); rb-j/RBJ, SkoomaDentist (r/DSP)
